1
00:01:40,820 --> 00:01:45,930
[THE DEVIL BETWEEN US]

2
00:01:45,950 --> 00:01:48,930
[Episode 4]

3
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:50,509
MIX CLUB

4
00:01:50,509 --> 00:01:51,350
is one of the few nightlife spots

5
00:01:51,350 --> 00:01:52,920
in the county.

6
00:01:53,160 --> 00:01:54,470
It doesn't open until 7:30 PM,

7
00:01:54,470 --> 00:01:56,830
so there's nothing to find if we go now.

8
00:01:57,880 --> 00:01:59,050
I've got an idea.

9
00:01:59,080 --> 00:02:01,000
Let's check out
the electronics factory first.

10
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:02,120
Lots of workers there—

11
00:02:02,120 --> 00:02:04,480
we might pick up what we need.

12
00:02:04,710 --> 00:02:06,480
Also, I've got a friend inside.

13
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:07,950
If we're going in to ask around,

14
00:02:07,950 --> 00:02:09,150
she can keep an eye out for us.

15
00:02:09,150 --> 00:02:11,950
It's easier
when you've got someone on the inside.

16
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:12,760
Hu Wenjing,

17
00:02:13,470 --> 00:02:14,670
I've thought it over.

18
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:16,510
Jin Longfeng's death

19
00:02:16,620 --> 00:02:17,570
wasn't on you.

20
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:19,470
As a detective,

21
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:22,090
you know Nuanhai Town better than I do.

22
00:02:22,710 --> 00:02:24,040
Director Dai was right;

23
00:02:24,079 --> 00:02:25,960
you're the best person for the job.

24
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:27,560
Let's put the past behind us.

25
00:02:27,750 --> 00:02:28,910
We were just doing our jobs.

26
00:02:28,910 --> 00:02:29,750
It's all work.

27
00:02:30,990 --> 00:02:31,520
Alright.

28
00:02:33,710 --> 00:02:34,030
Here's the plan.

29
00:02:34,030 --> 00:02:35,710
I'll reassign the tasks.

30
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:36,750
I'll head to the electronics factory

31
00:02:36,750 --> 00:02:38,750
and see what I can find later.

32
00:02:38,770 --> 00:02:40,500
You take Jin back to the station

33
00:02:41,070 --> 00:02:42,840
and go over the crime scene footage again.

34
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:43,240
Okay.

35
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:45,360
Let's put together
Liu Qiang's social connections.

36
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:46,480
When I get back,

37
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:48,280
we'll pool everything we've got.

38
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:49,750
Tonight we check out
that bar you mentioned—

39
00:02:49,750 --> 00:02:50,450
MIX CLUB.

40
00:02:50,470 --> 00:02:51,240
That bar.

41
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:51,800
It's settled.

42
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:52,430
Got it.

43
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:56,579
What are you doing?

44
00:02:57,329 --> 00:02:58,050
Hurry up!

45
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:16,310
You look pretty young.

46
00:03:16,310 --> 00:03:17,870
Did you just start working?

47
00:03:20,260 --> 00:03:21,260
Three years in.

48
00:03:23,150 --> 00:03:24,810
You look fresh out of college.

49
00:03:26,190 --> 00:03:29,990
I'm not interested in talking about
anything unrelated to the case.

50
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:35,520
What's your relationship with Yang Xinyu,
Liu Qiang's nephew?

51
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:36,720
We've met a few times.

52
00:03:36,920 --> 00:03:38,710
My dad is friends with Liu Qiang.

53
00:03:38,710 --> 00:03:39,630
They even tried to set up

54
00:03:39,630 --> 00:03:41,520
a blind date for me and Yang Xinyu.

55
00:03:44,079 --> 00:03:46,500
Since you've got
personal ties to the victim's family,

56
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:48,900
you should recuse yourself from this case.

57
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:54,310
You grew up in the city, didn't you?

58
00:03:54,310 --> 00:03:56,150
You don't get how small towns work.

59
00:03:56,150 --> 00:03:56,910
Around here, it's normal for everyone

60
00:03:56,910 --> 00:03:58,870
to know everyone.

61
00:03:59,350 --> 00:04:01,000
If we had to step aside every time

62
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:01,800
we knew someone,

63
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:02,840
no one would be left to do the job.

64
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:03,710
Narcotics cases

65
00:04:03,710 --> 00:04:05,680
fall under our jurisdiction.

66
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:07,310
You detectives shouldn't be
sticking your nose in.

67
00:04:07,310 --> 00:04:09,000
What do you mean by that?

68
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:11,590
Director Dai told us to coordinate.

69
00:04:11,590 --> 00:04:13,030
Even Qin's put his bias aside.

70
00:04:13,030 --> 00:04:14,000
If you've got a problem with me,

71
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:14,870
just say it.

72
00:04:14,890 --> 00:04:15,780
I don't.

73
00:04:24,240 --> 00:04:26,120
Jin Longfeng was your brother, wasn't he?

74
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:27,120
Who told you that?

75
00:04:27,270 --> 00:04:28,430
No one had to.

76
00:04:28,430 --> 00:04:29,960
The name, the resemblance…

77
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:31,800
The way you fixate on the Ding Lai case—

78
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:33,430
and the way you look at me.

79
00:04:34,790 --> 00:04:36,390
I know what you're thinking.

80
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:38,650
If you hadn't shown up that day,

81
00:04:38,830 --> 00:04:40,560
my brother wouldn't have died.

82
00:04:53,750 --> 00:04:54,610
Jin Longzheng,

83
00:04:54,950 --> 00:04:56,480
I didn't know your brother.

84
00:04:57,140 --> 00:04:57,680
But he was the first colleague

85
00:04:57,680 --> 00:04:59,390
I ever saw die in front of me.

86
00:04:59,390 --> 00:05:00,360
I'm sorry.

87
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:02,750
No one wants to watch

88
00:05:02,750 --> 00:05:04,010
their partner go down.

89
00:05:05,390 --> 00:05:06,040
But listen—

90
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:07,170
everyone knows what happened.

91
00:05:07,170 --> 00:05:08,520
It was an accident.

92
00:05:08,540 --> 00:05:09,870
It was just an accident.

93
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:12,190
I know what people are thinking—

94
00:05:12,190 --> 00:05:12,600
that if I

95
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:13,600
hadn't shown up that day,

96
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:15,040
maybe things would've
turned out differently.

97
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:16,390
Maybe Jin Longfeng wouldn't have died.

98
00:05:16,390 --> 00:05:17,720
I admit that is possible.

99
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:18,830
But it happened.

100
00:05:18,830 --> 00:05:20,030
We can't change that.

101
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:22,270
I've been a cop for ten years.

102
00:05:22,270 --> 00:05:24,920
Up before dawn, home past midnight.
I worked my ass off

103
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:26,240
to earn people's trust.

104
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:27,600
They thought I do a good job

105
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:29,040
and wanted to entrust me
with important tasks.

106
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:30,680
But just because of this one accident,

107
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:32,750
my reputation in the entire
Haizhou public security system,

108
00:05:32,750 --> 00:05:33,360
which I spent

109
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:36,620
almost a lifetime building up,
has completely collapsed.

110
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:37,880
Is that fair to me?

111
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:41,830
I understand you.

112
00:05:41,830 --> 00:05:43,190
You hate me when you see me.

113
00:05:43,190 --> 00:05:44,070
But even so,

114
00:05:44,830 --> 00:05:46,240
I will still cooperate fully with you,

115
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:47,500
because this is my job.

116
00:05:47,870 --> 00:05:49,390
If you really hate me that much,

117
00:05:49,390 --> 00:05:51,450
then turn that hatred into strength.

118
00:05:51,760 --> 00:05:54,120
Go catch those drug dealers and criminals.

119
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:55,630
Don't engage in infighting with me here.

120
00:05:55,630 --> 00:05:56,240
Okay?

121
00:06:12,690 --> 00:06:17,370
[Nuanfeng County People's Hospital]

122
00:06:19,390 --> 00:06:19,950
Director.

123
00:06:19,950 --> 00:06:20,600
Cheng Ken,

124
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:22,730
you're quite lucky.

125
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:23,920
You found a donor

126
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:25,770
whose HLA markers
are a perfect six-point match

127
00:06:25,770 --> 00:06:26,920
for your daughter.

128
00:06:27,330 --> 00:06:28,660
That's extremely rare.

129
00:06:32,150 --> 00:06:32,640
So,

130
00:06:33,159 --> 00:06:34,560
the surgery's possible?

131
00:06:38,480 --> 00:06:39,830
It must be my family

132
00:06:39,830 --> 00:06:40,630
up in heaven

133
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:42,460
watching over Jiajia.

134
00:06:42,960 --> 00:06:43,560
It's fine.

135
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:46,000
Since you've got a match,

136
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:46,830
I'll schedule the operation
as soon as possible.

137
00:06:46,830 --> 00:06:47,390
Okay.

138
00:06:47,659 --> 00:06:48,070
No.

139
00:06:48,070 --> 00:06:48,950
Not now.

140
00:06:49,210 --> 00:06:51,480
I haven't finalized things with the donor.

141
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:52,310
Whatever you pay them

142
00:06:52,310 --> 00:06:53,830
is between you and them.

143
00:06:54,070 --> 00:06:54,650
You've already prepaid

144
00:06:54,650 --> 00:06:56,610
the surgery fee.

145
00:06:56,870 --> 00:06:58,159
Though part of it
was used for Jiajia's hospitalization

146
00:06:58,159 --> 00:06:59,040
these past couple of days.

147
00:06:59,040 --> 00:06:59,480
Right.

148
00:07:00,050 --> 00:07:01,530
After the transplant,

149
00:07:01,730 --> 00:07:04,430
she must take
anti-rejection medication long term.

150
00:07:04,430 --> 00:07:06,690
Those, plus the necessary supplements,

151
00:07:06,780 --> 00:07:08,710
will run about 100,000 yuan a year.

152
00:07:09,790 --> 00:07:11,350
That's a heavy burden

153
00:07:11,510 --> 00:07:13,390
for most families.

154
00:07:14,270 --> 00:07:16,070
You need to be prepared for that.

155
00:07:16,430 --> 00:07:17,070
I know.

156
00:07:17,070 --> 00:07:18,070
I know.

157
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:25,390
Anyway, it's good news.

158
00:07:25,390 --> 00:07:25,950
Good news.

159
00:07:25,950 --> 00:07:26,390
Good news.

160
00:07:26,390 --> 00:07:26,990
Good news.

161
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:27,830
Thank you, Director.

162
00:07:27,830 --> 00:07:28,360
Okay.

163
00:07:28,880 --> 00:07:29,740
I'll get going.

164
00:07:53,650 --> 00:07:54,270
Xiaoyu,

165
00:07:54,270 --> 00:07:55,990
you're amazing.

166
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:15,750
Ken.

167
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:19,160
Are you busy?

168
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:19,690
Go ahead.

169
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:23,700
Can you lend me some money?

170
00:08:23,950 --> 00:08:24,560
Sure.

171
00:08:24,830 --> 00:08:25,960
How much do you need?

172
00:08:28,430 --> 00:08:30,160
What's the most you can lend me?

173
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:31,680
I told you before—

174
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:33,789
I can free up over 20,000 yuan.

175
00:08:35,390 --> 00:08:35,909
Okay.

176
00:08:36,549 --> 00:08:39,700
I already borrowed 50,000 yuan from you.

177
00:08:40,799 --> 00:08:43,330
And you can still come up
with another 20,000.

178
00:08:43,720 --> 00:08:45,270
I don't know what to say.

179
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:46,360
But

180
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:47,750
thank you.

181
00:08:47,750 --> 00:08:48,750
Thanks, brother.

182
00:08:48,930 --> 00:08:50,060
I'll remember this.

183
00:08:50,790 --> 00:08:51,750
We're brothers.

184
00:08:51,750 --> 00:08:53,280
Why are you being so polite?

185
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:55,630
I'll transfer it to you tomorrow.

186
00:08:55,630 --> 00:08:56,240
Thank you.

187
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:58,030
Bye.

188
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:15,320
Dad,

189
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:17,960
Xiaoyu is really good at puzzles.

190
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:19,440
Oh yeah? How so?

191
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:20,200
Look—

192
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:22,730
she put this big piece right here.

193
00:09:22,790 --> 00:09:24,360
And this one too.

194
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:26,410
She put all of these together.

195
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:29,300
She is pretty good.

196
00:09:29,550 --> 00:09:30,210
Don't be discouraged.

197
00:09:30,210 --> 00:09:31,410
Learn from her.

198
00:09:31,750 --> 00:09:32,610
Learn from her.

199
00:10:00,310 --> 00:10:06,410
[Common Drugs]

200
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:44,800
Who let you in?

201
00:10:48,390 --> 00:10:50,590
Wait, I just washed some grapes for you.

202
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:52,920
What's wrong?

203
00:10:59,130 --> 00:11:01,080
You interrupted my train of thought.

204
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:03,340
Why are you losing your temper like this?

205
00:11:07,280 --> 00:11:09,080
I'm going out for some fresh air.

206
00:11:09,120 --> 00:11:10,980
At this hour? Where are you going?

207
00:11:11,310 --> 00:11:12,080
Wang An!

208
00:12:32,890 --> 00:12:44,070
[MIX CLUB]

209
00:12:55,790 --> 00:12:57,390
You're eating way too fast.

210
00:12:57,390 --> 00:12:58,240
Didn't I tell you already?

211
00:12:58,240 --> 00:12:59,700
You can only take one a day.

212
00:13:01,040 --> 00:13:03,360
I stayed up late yesterday
trying to learn more.

213
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:04,630
Don't worry about my affairs.

214
00:13:04,630 --> 00:13:06,160
Just tell me if you have any.

215
00:13:09,510 --> 00:13:10,570
I only have five left.

216
00:13:10,570 --> 00:13:11,570
That's all I have.

217
00:13:11,760 --> 00:13:12,390
You have to promise me

218
00:13:12,390 --> 00:13:14,650
you won't come back for more for two days.

219
00:13:14,690 --> 00:13:16,220
Five for two days is enough.

220
00:13:17,750 --> 00:13:18,480
This time,

221
00:13:18,860 --> 00:13:19,760
it's 150 per pill.

222
00:13:19,760 --> 00:13:20,890
So it's 750 in total.

223
00:13:21,180 --> 00:13:22,580
Why is the price going up?

224
00:13:23,030 --> 00:13:24,030
The price is set by

225
00:13:24,030 --> 00:13:25,850
supply and demand.

226
00:13:26,280 --> 00:13:28,190
Good stuff like this
only gets more expensive.

227
00:13:28,190 --> 00:13:29,520
So, do you want it or not?

228
00:13:29,800 --> 00:13:31,260
If you don't, I'm leaving.

229
00:13:38,310 --> 00:13:39,510
I'll take it for 750.

230
00:13:40,910 --> 00:13:41,790
I'll transfer it to you later
from my phone.

231
00:13:41,790 --> 00:13:42,720
Transfer it now.

232
00:14:05,260 --> 00:14:05,940
Let's go.

233
00:14:06,560 --> 00:14:07,470
Come see me the day after tomorrow.

234
00:14:07,470 --> 00:14:08,390
Don't see me these two days.

235
00:14:08,390 --> 00:14:08,920
Bye-bye.

236
00:15:31,080 --> 00:15:31,840
Do you want anything else?

237
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:32,510
Hello.

238
00:15:34,790 --> 00:15:35,750
Do you have any beer?

239
00:15:35,750 --> 00:15:36,200
Yes.

240
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:41,480
This one.

241
00:15:49,320 --> 00:15:50,050
Scan it here?

242
00:15:50,310 --> 00:15:50,970
Yes, right.

243
00:15:57,360 --> 00:15:58,090
It's all set.

244
00:15:58,180 --> 00:15:58,670
Okay.

245
00:16:15,620 --> 00:16:16,750
Do you have anything

246
00:16:16,790 --> 00:16:18,510
a bit stronger?

247
00:16:19,670 --> 00:16:20,670
Whiskey?

248
00:16:20,670 --> 00:16:21,960
Or something else?

249
00:16:23,030 --> 00:16:23,720
No.

250
00:16:24,080 --> 00:16:25,280
I don't mean alcohol.

251
00:16:25,510 --> 00:16:26,320
Anything

252
00:16:26,670 --> 00:16:27,390
besides

253
00:16:27,390 --> 00:16:28,630
alcohol?

254
00:16:37,320 --> 00:16:38,120
Hey handsome,

255
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:41,700
is that guy looking for a girl?

256
00:16:41,710 --> 00:16:42,430
No.

257
00:16:42,790 --> 00:16:44,190
He wants that stuff.

258
00:16:47,670 --> 00:16:48,740
Wait a second.

259
00:16:48,810 --> 00:16:49,520
Alright.

260
00:16:55,420 --> 00:16:56,480
Hey there, friend.

261
00:16:56,550 --> 00:16:57,200
Hello.

262
00:16:57,960 --> 00:16:59,960
I heard you want to get a little high.

263
00:17:06,020 --> 00:17:06,869
You got some?

264
00:17:08,480 --> 00:17:09,920
How do you want to feel?

265
00:17:15,599 --> 00:17:16,319
Just...

266
00:17:20,310 --> 00:17:21,550
This isn't cheap.

267
00:17:22,450 --> 00:17:23,579
It's not cheap.

268
00:17:24,579 --> 00:17:25,380
How much is it?

269
00:17:26,829 --> 00:17:27,750
A gram...

270
00:17:28,020 --> 00:17:29,550
A gram costs a few thousand.

271
00:17:30,400 --> 00:17:31,350
How much a gram?

272
00:17:33,580 --> 00:17:35,380
It depends on what kind you want.

273
00:17:35,420 --> 00:17:36,280
The "off-grade,"

274
00:17:36,280 --> 00:17:37,100
the "mid-grade,"

275
00:17:37,100 --> 00:17:38,230
or the "top-grade"?

276
00:17:46,110 --> 00:17:46,870
What's the difference?

277
00:17:46,870 --> 00:17:47,800
What do you mean?

278
00:17:48,870 --> 00:17:50,070
It's your first time?

279
00:17:54,160 --> 00:17:55,090
Do you have some?

280
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:56,160
I don't.

281
00:17:56,920 --> 00:17:59,320
But I can connect you
with someone who does.

282
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:00,940
Sure.

283
00:18:00,960 --> 00:18:02,760
Please put me in touch with them.

284
00:18:02,920 --> 00:18:04,400
1,000 for the intro.

285
00:18:10,750 --> 00:18:11,640
No problem.

286
00:18:15,650 --> 00:18:16,370
Bro,

287
00:18:16,630 --> 00:18:17,500
come here.

288
00:18:22,030 --> 00:18:22,790
Is it safe?

289
00:18:23,740 --> 00:18:24,910
Of course it's safe.

290
00:18:24,930 --> 00:18:27,190
I've been running things here for years.

291
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:29,790
Can I meet him tonight?

292
00:18:30,940 --> 00:18:32,470
I'll take you there in a bit.

293
00:18:36,530 --> 00:18:37,450
Wait.

294
00:18:42,810 --> 00:18:43,670
Think about it.

295
00:18:44,480 --> 00:18:45,140
Don't rush.

296
00:19:02,710 --> 00:19:03,510
Here is 1,000.

297
00:19:04,970 --> 00:19:05,550
I'll take you there soon.

298
00:19:05,550 --> 00:19:06,200
Turn off the music!

299
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:07,330
Police inspection!

300
00:19:08,720 --> 00:19:09,410
Hurry up!

301
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:12,050
Police! Don't move!

302
00:19:13,440 --> 00:19:14,550
Show your ID.

303
00:19:15,510 --> 00:19:16,640
Do you have your ID?

304
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:17,830
Show your ID.

305
00:19:17,830 --> 00:19:18,960
Bro.

306
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:19,920
Give me my money back first.

307
00:19:19,920 --> 00:19:20,440
What are you doing?

308
00:19:20,440 --> 00:19:21,220
Not now.

309
00:19:21,250 --> 00:19:22,200
Give me the money back first.

310
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:22,980
Don't touch me now.

311
00:19:22,980 --> 00:19:23,640
What do you mean?

312
00:19:23,640 --> 00:19:24,400
What does this mean?

313
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:24,880
I don't know.

314
00:19:24,880 --> 00:19:26,480
I don't know what's going on.

315
00:19:26,550 --> 00:19:27,400
Does this happen often?

316
00:19:27,400 --> 00:19:28,350
No, it's never happened before.

317
00:19:28,350 --> 00:19:29,330
Take them to line up by the restrooms.

318
00:19:29,330 --> 00:19:30,200
Stand still.

319
00:19:30,270 --> 00:19:31,470
Go line up over there!

320
00:19:36,890 --> 00:19:38,400
Search the bags thoroughly.

321
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:39,590
Check the IDs.

322
00:19:40,120 --> 00:19:42,180
Did you find anything unusual today?

323
00:19:43,060 --> 00:19:44,300
Anything unusual?

324
00:19:46,590 --> 00:19:48,200
Did you notice any suspicious suspects

325
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:49,400
walking around here?

326
00:19:49,510 --> 00:19:50,030
Yes.

327
00:19:50,280 --> 00:19:50,960
Who was it?

328
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:52,920
Don't just check IDs.

329
00:19:53,450 --> 00:19:54,250
Liu!

330
00:19:56,920 --> 00:19:57,720
Wenjing.

331
00:19:57,940 --> 00:19:59,650
We've basically
got everyone under control.

332
00:19:59,650 --> 00:20:01,030
You can start questioning

333
00:20:01,030 --> 00:20:01,920
whenever you're ready.

334
00:20:01,920 --> 00:20:02,200
Okay.

335
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:03,790
We'll just do a quick sweep

336
00:20:03,790 --> 00:20:04,240
Alright.

337
00:20:04,240 --> 00:20:05,100
and ask around.

338
00:20:07,480 --> 00:20:08,590
Hurry up and pee.

339
00:20:08,590 --> 00:20:09,790
Stop stalling.

340
00:20:11,260 --> 00:20:11,910
Get in.

341
00:20:12,230 --> 00:20:13,090
You too, get in.

342
00:20:13,960 --> 00:20:14,760
Go to that one.

343
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:15,510
Get in.

344
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:16,640
Officer,

345
00:20:16,640 --> 00:20:17,160
what's going on?

346
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:17,920
Why are there so many cops tonight?

347
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:18,640
Not so many questions.

348
00:20:18,640 --> 00:20:19,270
Go in, quickly.

349
00:20:19,270 --> 00:20:19,920
You, that one.

350
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:20,400
Okay.

351
00:20:21,160 --> 00:20:23,090
Don't close the door. Keep it open.

352
00:20:24,360 --> 00:20:24,920
Pee.

353
00:20:25,790 --> 00:20:26,240
Wait,

354
00:20:27,310 --> 00:20:29,640
I can't pee with the door open
and so many people.

355
00:20:29,640 --> 00:20:32,440
What? Do you want to come back
to the station to pee?

356
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:33,640
I'll pee.

357
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:34,530
Pee.

358
00:20:45,660 --> 00:20:46,590
What's going on?

359
00:20:46,670 --> 00:20:47,400
Are you the one?

360
00:20:47,400 --> 00:20:48,240
What's the situation?

361
00:20:48,240 --> 00:20:48,770
Officer,

362
00:20:48,960 --> 00:20:50,020
just now at the bar,

363
00:20:50,230 --> 00:20:52,000
I saw two people buying something.

364
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:53,310
Did you see them make a deal?

365
00:20:53,310 --> 00:20:53,720
Yes, yes.

366
00:20:53,720 --> 00:20:56,050
Did you see exactly what they were buying?

367
00:20:56,910 --> 00:20:58,950
He said he was buying
something to get high.

368
00:20:58,950 --> 00:21:00,280
Where are those two now?

369
00:21:00,880 --> 00:21:01,830
They were just taken to the restroom.

370
00:21:01,830 --> 00:21:03,890
Where is the restroom? Take me there.

371
00:21:05,480 --> 00:21:05,920
Stop!

372
00:21:05,940 --> 00:21:06,410
Don't run!

373
00:21:06,410 --> 00:21:07,540
Freeze! Don't move!

374
00:21:14,170 --> 00:21:14,960
What are you looking at?

375
00:21:14,960 --> 00:21:15,790
Just focus on peeing.

376
00:21:15,790 --> 00:21:16,790
Stop stalling.

377
00:21:20,030 --> 00:21:20,920
Pin him down.

378
00:21:22,880 --> 00:21:23,790
Cuff him.

379
00:21:25,500 --> 00:21:26,300
What's wrong?

380
00:21:26,320 --> 00:21:27,900
Nothing. Someone just tried to run.

381
00:21:27,900 --> 00:21:28,530
We got him.

382
00:21:30,790 --> 00:21:31,200
Get in.

383
00:21:31,550 --> 00:21:32,280
Stay inside.

384
00:21:39,090 --> 00:21:39,850
Okay.

385
00:21:41,560 --> 00:21:42,420
Just those two.

386
00:21:42,720 --> 00:21:43,510
Which two?

387
00:21:44,240 --> 00:21:46,240
The fat guy in the floral shirt

388
00:21:46,310 --> 00:21:48,160
and the one with greasy hair.

389
00:21:48,160 --> 00:21:48,590
Okay, I got it.

390
00:21:48,590 --> 00:21:49,160
You can go back.

391
00:21:49,160 --> 00:21:49,640
Okay.

392
00:21:50,310 --> 00:21:51,590
None of your business.

393
00:21:51,740 --> 00:21:52,870
Go. Go wait outside.

394
00:21:56,700 --> 00:21:57,830
Don't go over there.

395
00:21:58,110 --> 00:21:59,160
Come back to the station with us.

396
00:21:59,160 --> 00:21:59,550
Me?

397
00:21:59,590 --> 00:22:00,110
What did I do?

398
00:22:00,110 --> 00:22:00,550
You'll find out

399
00:22:00,550 --> 00:22:01,200
when you get to the station.

400
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:01,440
Wait.

401
00:22:01,440 --> 00:22:03,640
My two friends are waiting for me there.

402
00:22:04,500 --> 00:22:05,210
Cheng Ken,

403
00:22:05,880 --> 00:22:07,210
what are you doing here?

404
00:22:08,550 --> 00:22:09,110
I...

405
00:22:10,120 --> 00:22:11,110
I just came to take a look.

406
00:22:11,110 --> 00:22:11,840
Look at what?

407
00:22:14,730 --> 00:22:15,790
I was just looking around.

408
00:22:15,790 --> 00:22:16,880
I've been really depressed lately.

409
00:22:16,880 --> 00:22:17,400
Don't go back.

410
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:19,200
Come back to the station with us.

411
00:22:19,350 --> 00:22:20,310
I just came to take a look.

412
00:22:20,310 --> 00:22:20,510
I didn't...

413
00:22:20,510 --> 00:22:21,400
We'll talk
when we get back to the station.

414
00:22:21,400 --> 00:22:21,930
Let's go.

415
00:22:22,350 --> 00:22:23,070
Hurry back.

416
00:22:36,050 --> 00:22:37,880
What's going on with the guy up ahead?

417
00:22:37,880 --> 00:22:39,810
He had some date-rape drugs on him.

418
00:22:40,110 --> 00:22:42,640
When we caught him, he tried to run,

419
00:22:42,640 --> 00:22:44,680
probably worried his family
or workplace would find out.

420
00:22:44,680 --> 00:22:46,160
And we caught him red-handed.

421
00:22:46,160 --> 00:22:46,670
Go.

422
00:23:04,110 --> 00:23:04,910
Director Dai.

423
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:08,690
Didn't you sleep all night?

424
00:23:09,920 --> 00:23:12,200
I still think this bar's suspicious,

425
00:23:12,880 --> 00:23:15,480
but staying here all night
didn't reveal anything.

426
00:23:15,480 --> 00:23:16,640
The two we brought back last night

427
00:23:16,640 --> 00:23:17,790
didn't lead us to anything either.

428
00:23:17,790 --> 00:23:19,310
One of them was just

429
00:23:19,310 --> 00:23:20,640
looking for some fun

430
00:23:20,640 --> 00:23:21,550
because life's been too stressful.

431
00:23:21,550 --> 00:23:23,080
The other was just a thug

432
00:23:23,100 --> 00:23:25,250
trying to scam some money.

433
00:23:25,720 --> 00:23:27,360
I spent the whole night
running around for nothing,

434
00:23:27,360 --> 00:23:28,890
and my throat's killing me.

435
00:23:30,030 --> 00:23:31,050
For cops,

436
00:23:31,070 --> 00:23:33,260
this is pretty normal.

437
00:23:34,070 --> 00:23:35,470
You should get some rest.

438
00:23:35,510 --> 00:23:37,240
Look at your face—

439
00:23:37,480 --> 00:23:38,880
it's the color of a potato.

440
00:23:38,880 --> 00:23:40,600
I'm fine. This afternoon I'll go...

441
00:23:40,600 --> 00:23:42,380
I need to check Liu Qiang's
social connections.

442
00:23:42,380 --> 00:23:43,840
That hasn't been done yet.

443
00:23:44,640 --> 00:23:45,840
Are you not picking up the kid

444
00:23:45,840 --> 00:23:46,840
this afternoon?

445
00:23:47,240 --> 00:23:47,720
Yeah.

446
00:23:49,310 --> 00:23:50,680
It's fine; my dad is there.

447
00:23:50,680 --> 00:23:51,160
You

448
00:23:51,160 --> 00:23:52,400
take a break when you can.

449
00:23:52,400 --> 00:23:53,070
I'm fine.

450
00:23:53,560 --> 00:23:54,320
Okay.

451
00:23:57,490 --> 00:23:57,960
Sorry.

452
00:23:57,960 --> 00:23:58,510
Why are you so startled?

453
00:23:58,510 --> 00:23:59,200
I'm clearing my throat.

454
00:23:59,200 --> 00:23:59,830
I, uh...

455
00:24:00,470 --> 00:24:01,800
I need to wake myself up.

456
00:24:01,880 --> 00:24:02,680
Get some rest.

457
00:24:03,410 --> 00:24:05,140
What's wrong with your throat?

458
00:24:22,160 --> 00:24:22,960
Cao Jinchuan!

459
00:24:23,350 --> 00:24:24,070
Wake up!

460
00:24:36,440 --> 00:24:37,040
That's it?

461
00:24:39,640 --> 00:24:40,500
Are you sleepy?

462
00:24:41,270 --> 00:24:42,110
Wait, sir…

463
00:24:42,440 --> 00:24:43,070
I've told you

464
00:24:43,070 --> 00:24:43,680
everything

465
00:24:43,680 --> 00:24:44,630
I needed to.

466
00:24:46,070 --> 00:24:46,800
Print it out.

467
00:24:48,270 --> 00:24:49,110
Look at that.

468
00:24:49,790 --> 00:24:51,450
Sir, you've got good insight.

469
00:24:52,030 --> 00:24:52,880
Be serious.

470
00:24:53,480 --> 00:24:55,680
Remember, we can call you back anytime.

471
00:24:55,960 --> 00:24:56,710
Understood.

472
00:24:59,110 --> 00:24:59,680
Officer,

473
00:25:01,790 --> 00:25:03,120
is there anything else?

474
00:25:05,480 --> 00:25:07,960
My daughter is home alone.

475
00:25:08,310 --> 00:25:10,310
I'm worried she'll wake up

476
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:11,920
and be scared if I'm not there.

477
00:25:11,920 --> 00:25:13,000
Could I…

478
00:25:14,890 --> 00:25:15,690
Director Dai.

479
00:25:33,720 --> 00:25:34,300
Hello.

480
00:25:54,160 --> 00:25:54,820
Take a look.

481
00:25:55,270 --> 00:25:56,730
If everything looks fine,

482
00:25:56,750 --> 00:25:57,350
please sign here

483
00:25:57,350 --> 00:25:58,810
and put your fingerprint.

484
00:25:59,070 --> 00:25:59,680
Same here—

485
00:25:59,680 --> 00:26:00,090
just put a fingerprint

486
00:26:00,090 --> 00:26:00,890
here too.

487
00:26:17,310 --> 00:26:18,910
Officer, may I ask your name?

488
00:26:19,480 --> 00:26:20,540
My last name's Jin.

489
00:26:20,590 --> 00:26:21,320
Officer Jin,

490
00:26:23,440 --> 00:26:25,350
I've learned my lesson today.

491
00:26:25,920 --> 00:26:27,360
It won't happen again, I promise.

492
00:26:27,360 --> 00:26:28,820
Thank you for helping me out.

493
00:26:28,820 --> 00:26:29,590
Thank you.

494
00:26:37,430 --> 00:26:38,060
Go.

495
00:26:50,680 --> 00:26:51,270
Morning.

496
00:26:52,510 --> 00:26:53,070
Ken,

497
00:26:53,830 --> 00:26:55,400
why are you only getting here now?

498
00:26:55,400 --> 00:26:56,030
I...

499
00:26:56,510 --> 00:26:58,470
I forgot about the overtime today.

500
00:26:58,680 --> 00:27:01,410
I took my daughter to the hospital
for a check-up.

501
00:27:01,720 --> 00:27:02,720
Is she sick again?

502
00:27:07,090 --> 00:27:07,960
Listen,

503
00:27:08,240 --> 00:27:09,590
Mr. Sun came by looking for you earlier.
He couldn't find you

504
00:27:09,590 --> 00:27:10,790
and got really mad.

505
00:27:12,270 --> 00:27:13,130
What happened?

506
00:27:13,920 --> 00:27:16,580
You didn't book
the outreach invoices, did you?

507
00:27:16,960 --> 00:27:17,240
Right.

508
00:27:17,240 --> 00:27:17,890
I forgot.

509
00:27:17,910 --> 00:27:19,000
I haven't gone to see them yet.

510
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:20,200
Why go to them?

511
00:27:20,200 --> 00:27:21,350
Why don't you get it?

512
00:27:21,350 --> 00:27:22,070
Ken,

513
00:27:24,160 --> 00:27:25,550
isn't that a bit much?

514
00:27:26,200 --> 00:27:27,830
Everyone in the department
is working overtime today,

515
00:27:27,830 --> 00:27:29,090
and you're still late.

516
00:27:29,160 --> 00:27:30,220
I'm sorry, Mr. Sun.

517
00:27:30,550 --> 00:27:31,440
Something came up at home last night.

518
00:27:31,440 --> 00:27:32,200
Come with me.

519
00:27:49,960 --> 00:27:50,680
Ken,

520
00:27:51,440 --> 00:27:52,200
I actually

521
00:27:52,510 --> 00:27:53,960
do appreciate

522
00:27:54,200 --> 00:27:55,540
your work ethic.

523
00:27:58,600 --> 00:27:59,270
Thank you.

524
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:00,830
But

525
00:28:02,270 --> 00:28:04,790
this matter wasn't handled well.

526
00:28:06,200 --> 00:28:08,440
Last time when I treated the
whole department to dinner,

527
00:28:08,440 --> 00:28:09,500
I made it clear that

528
00:28:09,780 --> 00:28:10,870
those in finance

529
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:12,790
need to be flexible

530
00:28:12,960 --> 00:28:14,200
and not so rigid.

531
00:28:14,830 --> 00:28:15,530
Right?

532
00:28:19,310 --> 00:28:19,680
Right.

533
00:28:19,680 --> 00:28:21,080
I understand your point.

534
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:24,070
But our factory

535
00:28:24,070 --> 00:28:25,960
has an internal audit system.

536
00:28:26,270 --> 00:28:28,070
You take two days off every week,

537
00:28:28,480 --> 00:28:30,890
and I've never made things
difficult for you,

538
00:28:30,890 --> 00:28:31,440
right?

539
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:32,960
Yes.

540
00:28:33,440 --> 00:28:34,510
I really appreciate everything

541
00:28:34,510 --> 00:28:36,970
you've done for me,
and I haven't forgotten.

542
00:28:40,350 --> 00:28:42,660
But these invoices really can't be filed—

543
00:28:42,660 --> 00:28:43,580
they're risky,

544
00:28:44,110 --> 00:28:45,570
and the risk is pretty big.

545
00:28:46,790 --> 00:28:48,170
If it's discovered,

546
00:28:48,290 --> 00:28:49,660
I could lose my job.

547
00:28:50,190 --> 00:28:52,390
You know about my family situation too.

548
00:28:59,880 --> 00:29:00,680
I understand.

549
00:29:06,230 --> 00:29:06,750
Look,

550
00:29:06,790 --> 00:29:08,320
don't worry about this one.

551
00:29:08,590 --> 00:29:09,790
I'll let Wu handle it.

552
00:29:10,030 --> 00:29:11,350
She's more flexible than you

553
00:29:11,350 --> 00:29:12,810
and has a brighter future.

554
00:29:27,030 --> 00:29:28,510
After the transplant,

555
00:29:28,680 --> 00:29:31,350
must take anti-rejection medication
long term.

556
00:29:31,350 --> 00:29:32,030
Those,

557
00:29:32,030 --> 00:29:33,680
plus the necessary supplements,

558
00:29:33,680 --> 00:29:35,610
will run about 100,000 yuan a year.

559
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:47,620
Mr. Sun.

560
00:29:49,030 --> 00:29:51,360
I didn't express myself clearly just now.

561
00:29:53,920 --> 00:29:55,350
I can take this risk.

562
00:29:57,790 --> 00:30:00,590
But can the outreach team
be a little flexible too?

563
00:30:08,790 --> 00:30:09,880
You surprise me.

564
00:30:17,200 --> 00:30:18,090
Alright,

565
00:30:24,410 --> 00:30:26,010
go see the contact over there

566
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:27,860
and talk to him.

567
00:30:34,790 --> 00:30:35,390
Thank you.

568
00:31:38,750 --> 00:31:39,550
You're like

569
00:31:41,510 --> 00:31:43,840
one of those instant noodles come to life.

570
00:31:44,640 --> 00:31:45,640
What? Instant noodles?

571
00:31:45,640 --> 00:31:46,480
I'm way paler

572
00:31:46,480 --> 00:31:47,310
than that.

573
00:31:49,350 --> 00:31:50,350
A lot has happened

574
00:31:51,640 --> 00:31:53,110
this month.

575
00:31:53,550 --> 00:31:54,350
Yeah.

576
00:31:55,710 --> 00:31:57,200
Why are you so sleepy?

577
00:31:57,550 --> 00:31:59,010
Did you stay up late again?

578
00:31:59,590 --> 00:32:00,310
Don't remind me.

579
00:32:00,310 --> 00:32:02,270
I was watching surveillance footage
all night—

580
00:32:02,270 --> 00:32:03,400
didn't find a thing.

581
00:32:03,640 --> 00:32:05,170
There wasn't a single lead.

582
00:32:05,880 --> 00:32:07,200
But I did see Wang An

583
00:32:07,200 --> 00:32:09,200
hanging around outside that bar.

584
00:32:09,940 --> 00:32:11,110
I mean, instead of studying,

585
